1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,040
Can I please have your attention?

2
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:05,040
Ryan and I have a huge announcement.

3
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:07,040
Oh, my gosh!

4
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:08,040
Wow.

5
00:00:08,040 --> 00:00:11,040
Over the weekend, Ryan, Bailey, Howard, and I got divorced.

6
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:14,040
Sweet free ring!

7
00:00:14,040 --> 00:00:15,040
Divorced?

8
00:00:15,040 --> 00:00:17,040
Just so you know, it's totally amicable.

9
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:18,040
We're fine.

10
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:20,040
We don't need people here to take sides.

11
00:00:20,040 --> 00:00:22,040
The last thing that we want is any kind of drama.

12
00:00:22,040 --> 00:00:24,040
Wait, I... Can you back up?

13
00:00:24,040 --> 00:00:25,040
What's the story?

14
00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:27,040
We were having a beautiful weekend in the Poconos.

15
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:29,040
We were making love constantly.

16
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:30,080
We saw the sunrise.

17
00:00:30,080 --> 00:00:31,080
Ryan was crying a lot.

18
00:00:31,080 --> 00:00:33,080
That's not a relevant detail.

19
00:00:33,080 --> 00:00:35,080
And in the morning, we walked by a chapel,

20
00:00:35,080 --> 00:00:37,080
and we stopped suddenly, and Ryan said,

21
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:40,080
I don't think I should be married to you anymore.

22
00:00:41,080 --> 00:00:42,080
Wait.

23
00:00:42,080 --> 00:00:44,080
I'm sorry, when did you get married?

24
00:00:44,080 --> 00:00:46,080
Um, like a week ago.

25
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:48,080
We got really wasted and it just felt right.

26
00:00:48,080 --> 00:00:49,080
You didn't invite any of us?

27
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:51,080
We are getting divorced, Andy!

28
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:53,080
This is such a raw time.

29
00:00:53,080 --> 00:00:55,080
God, baby, you know, with people's reactions to this,

30
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:57,080
I wonder if we made a mistake.

31
00:00:57,120 --> 00:00:59,120
No, with the messed up laws in this country,

32
00:00:59,120 --> 00:01:02,120
I don't want to be married until everyone can be married.

33
00:01:02,120 --> 00:01:03,120
You know what, Ryan?

34
00:01:03,120 --> 00:01:06,120
I talked to the other gay guys, and we're okay with it.

35
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:08,120
We all agree it's time for you to get married.

36
00:01:08,120 --> 00:01:10,120
No, no, Oscar, not until everyone can.

37
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:12,120
Ryan, I changed my mind.

38
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,120
Okay, fine.

39
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:14,120
You know what?

40
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:16,120
This actually isn't amicable at all,

41
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:18,120
and we actually do need people to take sides.

42
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:20,120
Who's on my side?

43
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:23,120
And who is on my side?

44
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:28,120
I'm sorry.

45
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:50,120
Alright, bye.

46
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:51,120
Bye!

47
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,120
Let's go!

48
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,120
Just a minute!

49
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:54,120
How long do we have to wait?

50
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,120
For what?

51
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,160
You broke up with AJ weeks ago.

52
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:59,160
Don't you have a sales call to go on?

53
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,160
I don't understand.

54
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:01,160
I really don't.

55
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:03,160
I mean, we know we're going to start dating.

56
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:04,160
Why not now?

57
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:05,160
We don't know that.

58
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:06,160
Sure we do.

59
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:08,160
Why is it such a certainty that we're supposed to be together?

60
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:10,160
Why does the sun rise in the morning?

61
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:12,160
Why do magnets stick together?

62
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:13,160
Because everybody says so.

63
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:14,160
Everybody.

64
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:16,160
Michael, I can't keep getting into a situation

65
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:18,160
where I date whoever I'm working with.

66
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:20,160
You can understand that.

67
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:21,160
No, I understand.

68
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:22,160
I just don't agree.

69
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:24,160
Well, you don't have to agree.

70
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,200
Yes, I do.

71
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:26,200
No, you don't.

72
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:27,200
Yes, I do.

73
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:29,200
No, you can have your own opinion.

74
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:32,200
I have my own opinion and my opinion is to disagree with you.

75
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:35,200
Please give me a lot of fun to drive around a car with.

76
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:36,200
You'll get through it, hon.

77
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:38,200
Just make a game out of it.

78
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:39,200
Funny gym game.

79
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,200
That's it?

80
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:43,200
That's all I get?

81
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:46,200
Even after all the hard work I put into celebrating your talent today?

82
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:48,200
Alright, what'd you do?

83
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:51,200
Well, those things that you consider doodles, I consider art.

84
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,200
Where'd you put it?

85
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,200
Where'd I put what?

86
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,200
Let's go.

87
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,200
Oh, sorry, I gotta go.

88
00:02:58,200 --> 00:02:59,200
Say it, where?

89
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:00,200
Okay, fine, three hints.

90
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:03,200
One, when you're getting colder, you're really getting warmer.

91
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:04,200
The fridge.

92
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:07,200
Two, you have a better chance if you think Bob Vance.

93
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,200
The fridge, got it.

94
00:03:08,200 --> 00:03:09,200
And a final clue.

95
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,200
Let's go!

96
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:11,200
You know what, just think about it.

97
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:12,200
You'll be fine.

98
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,200
Bye.

99
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:17,200
Holly is ruining Michael's life.

100
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:22,200
He thinks she's so special and she's so not.

101
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:24,240
Her personality is like a three.

102
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,240
Her sense of humor is a two.

103
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:29,240
Her ears are like a seven and a four.

104
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:31,240
Add it all up and what do you get?

105
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,240
Sixteen.

106
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:34,240
And he treats her like she's a perfect forty.

107
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,240
It's nuts.

108
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:44,240
Cheer up, we made a sale.

109
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:46,240
Just drive faster, I wanna get back.

110
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,240
I'm going the speed limit.

111
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:49,240
Okay, fine.

112
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:51,240
My feelings don't matter to you.

113
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:53,280
It matters to you is your precious speed limit.

114
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:55,280
Someone's in a bad mood.

115
00:03:55,280 --> 00:03:56,280
No, I'm not.

116
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,280
I'm not in a bad mood.

117
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:03,280
I'm not, Jim.

118
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,280
Hello?

119
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,280
Okay, fine, ignore me.

120
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,280
Have it your way.

121
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:10,280
Let's just talk about you, as always.

122
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:13,280
Sex different after the baby, Jim?

123
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,280
Alright, let me turn on some music.

124
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:15,280
I need to pee.

125
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,280
No, you don't.
